        walkthrough = '1. Speak with Ghatsad in the Automaton Workshop (I-7) in Aht Urhgan Whitegate for a cutscene.\n   - You will receive a [Key Item]Gift for Megomak.\n2. Head to Mount Zhayolm (I-9) via the Halvung Staging Point and examine the Acid-eaten Door for a cutscene (near Cerberus spawn. This is on the second level, follow the ramp up from the central part of I-8).\n   - This door lies beyond the Gates of Halvung near the Halvung Staging Point, not the other one at (H-8).\n     - You will need a [Key Item]Cast metal plate to open the gate. See the page if you lack the KI.\n     - It is in the far northwest corner of (I-9), on the upper level of the Troll structures.\n     - Once the door is opened, keep going south up the ramparts, and through an arch. On the right will be the house of Megomak.\n3. Proceed to Hazhalm Testing Grounds in Caedarva Mire (Einherjar\'s location) and examine the Entry Gate for another cutscene with Uran-Mafran and the Destiny Destroyers.\n   - The quickest transportation is to Caedarva Mire Home Point #1.\n   - Completing the quest "A Stygian Pact" will unlock an extra dialogue option with regards to Odin.\n4. Head outside to Caedarva Mire and examine the Vexing Sniffles (E-10) (Graveyard, outside of Hazhalm zone) for a cutscene.\n5. Examine the Vexing Sniffles once more to begin a confrontation against Gloom Phantom (WAR/DRK), Magh Bihu (MNK), and Dazbog (PLD).\n   - Approximately 60k HP each.\n   - Mnejing will assist and must be kept alive.\n     - Note:  You must bring the enemies close to Mnejing to engage immediately, otherwise he will despawn and the fight will end prematurely.\n     - You will receive a [Key Item]Pure white ampoule after the fight.\n   - Similar to TVR Mission 1-4 "The Destiny Destroyers," the Gloom Phantom and Dazbog can attempt skillchains if they focus the same target.\n     - However, Magh Bihu will no longer attempt Magic Bursts afterward but can use Hundred Fists repeatedly.\n6. Examine the Vexing Sniffles a final time for a cutscene.\n7. Return to the Acid-eaten Door in Mount Zhayolm at (I-9) for a cutscene.\n8. Return to Ghatsad (I-7) in Aht Urhgan Whitegate for the final cutscene and your reward.',
