    ['To Movalpolos!'] = {
        id = 552,
        start_npc = 'Gumbah',
        start_zone = 'Bastok Mines',
        start_pos = 'J-7',
        description = 'Mission Orders: According to Gumbah, a Galka has been sighted in a place known as Movalpolos. You have been asked to inform him that the gate has already been sealed. To Movalpolos!',
        reward = '20,000 Gil',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'The Prime Weapons'},
        next = {'Magh Bihu on the Prowl'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Gumbah in Bastok Mines (HP#3) at (J-7) inside a house on the upper walkway, in the back room, for a cutscene.\n2. Speak to Tarnotik in Oldton Movalpolos (K-10) for a cutscene.\n3. To reach Tarnotik, the best options are:\n   - The Proto-Waypoint warp takes you to (K-10), which is closest.\n   - Survival Guide to Movalpolos.\n   - Using Escape in Newton Movalpolos and zoning into Oldton Movalpolos puts you at the Survival Guide. Run east to Tarnotik at (K-10).\n4. To unlock the Proto-Waypoint, travel through Newton Movalpolos.\n5. While in Oldton Movalpolos, travel to (E-13), talk to Twinkbrix and trade 2,716 gil for teleportation to Mine Shaft #2716.\n6. Exit into Newton Movalpolos, and travel to the furnace at (K-8).\n7. You will be heading south from here. If the fence/gate is restricting you from going south. You will need a Firesand.\n   - You may farm one from Moblin Roadman/Engineer/Headman.\n8. Trade the Firesand to the furnace to move the fence/gate.\n9. Drop off at (I/J-9), and continue running south.\n10. Head to (E-9) (4 on the Map), and exit back into Oldton Movalpolos.\n11. The Geomagnetic Fount is on the left near the opening of the tunnel.\n----\n12. Alternatively, take the Home Point to Newton Movalpolos and walk through the revolving gate (may need a Firesand).\n13. Go south towards exit 4 on the map by dropping down at (J-9), and zone back into Oldton Movalpolos.\n14. Next, travel to Mine Shaft #2716 and interact with the Shaft Entrance for a cutscene.\n   - Tarnotik will warp you to Mine Shaft #2716 if you trade a Snow Lily to him.\n   - The Home Point warp to Newton Movalpolos is closest.\n   - Otherwise, Twinkbrix in Oldton Movalpolos will warp you directly to Mine Shaft #2716 if you trade 10k Gil.\n     - Use the Oldton Movalpolos Survival Guide.\n15. After the cutscene, interact with the BCNM entrance again and select To Movalpolos! to enter the battlefield.\n16. The fight is against Gloom Phantom, Awoken Vampyr Jarl, Awoken Ariri Samariri (has access to Death), and Awoken Hildesvini.\n   - Trusts may be used in the fight.\n   - Jabbos will assist and can tank one mob while you work on the rest.\n     - He will engage the enemy upon drawing your weapon, regardless of your distance to the enemy.\n17. After the fight, you will automatically enter a cutscene and receive your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
