        previous = {'Raebrimm\'s Rebirth'},
        next = {'Koru-Moru\'s Hypothesis'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak with Dancing Wolf in Rabao (G-6) HP #2 for a cutscene to begin the mission.\n2. Zone into Quicksand Caves from the Altepa Gate for a cutscene. The entrance is in Western Altepa Desert at (I-6/7).\n   - See the Altepa Gate page for instructions on how to open the Altepa Gate.\n3. The fight with Uran-Mafran (BLM/RDM) will immediately begin once you touch the Journey\'s End at (K-10).\n   - Has approximately 185k HP.\n   - Trusts may be used in this fight.\n   - Uran-Mafran can use  Manafont multiple times and has a very high degree of Fast Cast\n     -  Manafont will remove all applied debuffs.\n   - Possesses a substantial resistance to silence (though not immunity). Other enfeebles landed normally.\n     - Seen using BLM -jas, Cure VI, Enspells, Protect V, Shell V, Meteor, Impact, Comet, and AoE enfeebles.\n     -  Manafont will make short work of any trusts. Recommended to kill quickly or attempt to land silence.\n   - Will attempt to self-skillchain with Club Weapon Skills and magic burst accordingly.\n     - Black Halo and tier VI magic bursts hit hard. Damage taken gear is highly recommended.\n     - Possesses large amounts of regain and can complete skillchains even if unable to land regular hits.\n     - Trust tanks will not survive magic bursts. They can deal over 10k damage.\n   - You will be joined by Oggbi (MNK), who must be kept alive.\n     - Can use  Hundred Fists multiple times and various Hand-to-Hand weaponskills.\n4. Touch the Journey\'s End afterwards for a cutscene.\n     - Credit for beating Uran-Mafran is retained even if your character is defeated.\n5. Speak with Gumbah in Bastok Mines (J-7) HP #1 for the final cutscene and your reward.',
